# Product triage (vision alignment)

When the user asks to **prioritize issues**, **review enhancements**, **what to build next**, or uses **`/product-triage`**:

Follow `.cursor/skills/product-triage/SKILL.md`:

1. Ensure RepoNerve memory (`reponerve init && reponerve scan` if needed)
2. Load vision context via `reponerve ask` + `docs/vision/vision.md` + `docs/roadmap/v1.x-backlog.md`
3. Fetch issues: `./scripts/product-triage-issues.sh` or `gh issue list`
4. Score with rubric in `.cursor/skills/product-triage/reference.md`
5. Run `reuse-check` before recommending new subsystems
6. Output the triage report table format from the skill

Do not recommend out-of-scope items (semantic search, cloud core, autonomous commits, federation) without explicitly flagging RFC + vision conflict.
